        <entry key="$PROJECT_DIR$/index.html">
          <value>
            <PendingDiffInfo>
              <option name="filePath" value="$PROJECT_DIR$/index.html" />
              <option name="originalContent" value="&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;&#10;&lt;html lang='en'&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;head&gt;&#10;    &lt;base href=&quot;.&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;link rel=&quot;shortcut icon&quot; type=&quot;image/png&quot; href=&quot;assets/favicon.png&quot;/&gt;&#10;    &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; type=&quot;text/css&quot; media=&quot;all&quot; href=&quot;assets/main.css&quot;/&gt;&#10;    &lt;meta name=&quot;description&quot; content=&quot;The 2nd Greater Bay Area Physical Science Young Scientist Forum, June 5-6, 2026, The Chinese University of Hong Kong&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;meta name=&quot;resource-type&quot; content=&quot;document&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;meta name=&quot;distribution&quot; content=&quot;global&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;meta name=&quot;KeyWords&quot; content=&quot;Forum 2026, Greater Bay Area, Physical Science, Young Scientist, CUHK, Hong Kong&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;title&gt;Forum 2026 &amp;ndash; The 2nd Greater Bay Area Physical Science Young Scientist Forum&lt;/title&gt;&#10;&lt;/head&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;body&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;div class=&quot;banner&quot;&gt;&#10;        &lt;img src=&quot;assets/banner.png&quot; alt=&quot;Forum 2026 Banner&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;/div&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;table class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;        &lt;tr&gt;&#10;            &lt;td class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;                &lt;a class=&quot;current&quot; title=&quot;Conference Home Page&quot; href=&quot;.&quot;&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&#10;            &lt;/td&gt;&#10;            &lt;td class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;                &lt;a title=&quot;Register for the Conference&quot; href=&quot;registration&quot;&gt;Registration&lt;/a&gt;&#10;            &lt;/td&gt;&#10;            &lt;td class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;                &lt;a title=&quot;Conference Program&quot; href=&quot;program&quot;&gt;Program&lt;/a&gt; &#10;            &lt;/td&gt;&#10;            &lt;td class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;                &lt;a title=&quot;Directions to the Conference&quot; href=&quot;directions&quot;&gt;Directions&lt;/a&gt;&#10;            &lt;/td&gt;&#10;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#10;    &lt;/table&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;h2&gt;About Forum 2026&lt;/h2&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        The 2nd Greater Bay Area Physical Science Young Scientist Forum (&amp;ldquo;Forum 2026&amp;rdquo;) will take place from &lt;strong&gt;June 5 to 6, 2026&lt;/strong&gt; at &lt;strong&gt;The Chinese University of Hong Kong (CUHK)&lt;/strong&gt;, Hong Kong, China.&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        Following the success of the 1st Forum held at CUHK-Shenzhen in 2025 (initiated by Prof. Benzhong Tang), we are very honored to host the 2nd of its kind. Forum 2026 aims to continue growing into an annual flagship event for Young Scholars (particularly tenure-tracked junior faculties) in Physical Sciences in universities in the Greater Bay Area. With high concentration of young faculties, the Forum hopes to encourage active peer discussions and initiate early collaborations.&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        In addition to traditional physical science subjects, Forum 2026 also invites frontier topics in &lt;strong&gt;materials science&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;quantum technologies&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;energy and environmental solutions&lt;/strong&gt;, and other &lt;strong&gt;interdisciplinary physical sciences&lt;/strong&gt;.&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;h2&gt;Organizing Committee&lt;/h2&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        &lt;strong&gt;Conference Secretary (&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:forum2026cuhk@gmail.com&quot;&gt;forum2026cuhk@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt;):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#10;        Dr. Wang Gang, Dr. Han Peng, Ms. Jingyi Liu (Webmaster)&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        &lt;strong&gt;Local Organizing Committee (&lt;a href=&quot;yechen@cuhk.edu.hk&quot;&gt;yechen@cuhk.edu.hk&lt;/a&gt;):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#10;        Prof. Ye Chen (Chair), Prof. Xinglong Zhang (Co-Chair), Prof. Hung Wing Li, Prof. Hairong Lyu, Prof. Qisi Wang, Prof. Qingyun Wan&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        &lt;strong&gt;Advisory Board:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#10;        Prof. Chunshan Song, Prof. Hua Zhang, Prof. To Ngai&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;footer&gt;&#10;        &amp;copy; Forum 2026 Organizing Committee&#10;        &amp;nbsp;|&amp;nbsp; Design by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mikepierce&quot;&gt;Mike Pierce&lt;/a&gt;&#10;    &lt;/footer&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;/body&gt;&#10;&lt;/html&gt;&#10;&#10;" />
              <option name="updatedContent" value="&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;&#10;&lt;html lang='en'&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;head&gt;&#10;    &lt;base href=&quot;.&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;link rel=&quot;shortcut icon&quot; type=&quot;image/png&quot; href=&quot;assets/favicon.png&quot;/&gt;&#10;    &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; type=&quot;text/css&quot; media=&quot;all&quot; href=&quot;assets/main.css&quot;/&gt;&#10;    &lt;meta name=&quot;description&quot; content=&quot;The 2nd Greater Bay Area Physical Science Young Scientist Forum, June 5-6, 2026, The Chinese University of Hong Kong&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;meta name=&quot;resource-type&quot; content=&quot;document&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;meta name=&quot;distribution&quot; content=&quot;global&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;meta name=&quot;KeyWords&quot; content=&quot;Forum 2026, Greater Bay Area, Physical Science, Young Scientist, CUHK, Hong Kong&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;title&gt;Forum 2026 &amp;ndash; The 2nd Greater Bay Area Physical Science Young Scientist Forum&lt;/title&gt;&#10;&lt;/head&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;body&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;div class=&quot;banner&quot;&gt;&#10;        &lt;img src=&quot;assets/banner.png&quot; alt=&quot;Forum 2026 Banner&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;/div&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;table class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;        &lt;tr&gt;&#10;            &lt;td class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;                &lt;a class=&quot;current&quot; title=&quot;Conference Home Page&quot; href=&quot;.&quot;&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&#10;            &lt;/td&gt;&#10;            &lt;td class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;                &lt;a title=&quot;Abstract Submission&quot; href=&quot;registration&quot;&gt;Abstract Submission&lt;/a&gt;&#10;            &lt;/td&gt;&#10;            &lt;td class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;                &lt;a title=&quot;Presentation Schedule&quot; href=&quot;program&quot;&gt;Presentation Schedule&lt;/a&gt; &#10;            &lt;/td&gt;&#10;            &lt;td class=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;&#10;                &lt;a title=&quot;Conference Venue and Transportation&quot; href=&quot;directions&quot;&gt;Conference Venue and Transportation&lt;/a&gt;&#10;            &lt;/td&gt;&#10;        &lt;/tr&gt;&#10;    &lt;/table&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;h2&gt;About Forum 2026&lt;/h2&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        The 2nd Greater Bay Area Physical Science Young Scientist Forum (&amp;ldquo;Forum 2026&amp;rdquo;) will take place from &lt;strong&gt;June 5 to 6, 2026&lt;/strong&gt; at &lt;strong&gt;The Chinese University of Hong Kong (CUHK)&lt;/strong&gt;, Hong Kong, China.&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        Following the success of the 1st Forum held at CUHK-Shenzhen in 2025 (initiated by Prof. Benzhong Tang), we are very honored to host the 2nd of its kind. Forum 2026 aims to continue growing into an annual flagship event for Young Scholars (particularly tenure-tracked junior faculties) in Physical Sciences in universities in the Greater Bay Area. With high concentration of young faculties, the Forum hopes to encourage active peer discussions and initiate early collaborations.&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        In addition to traditional physical science subjects, Forum 2026 also invites frontier topics in &lt;strong&gt;materials science&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;quantum technologies&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;energy and environmental solutions&lt;/strong&gt;, and other &lt;strong&gt;interdisciplinary physical sciences&lt;/strong&gt;.&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;h2&gt;Organizing Committee&lt;/h2&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        &lt;strong&gt;Conference Secretary (&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:forum2026cuhk@gmail.com&quot;&gt;forum2026cuhk@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt;):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#10;        Dr. Wang Gang, Dr. Han Peng, Ms. Jingyi Liu (Webmaster)&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        &lt;strong&gt;Local Organizing Committee (&lt;a href=&quot;yechen@cuhk.edu.hk&quot;&gt;yechen@cuhk.edu.hk&lt;/a&gt;):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#10;        Prof. Ye Chen (Chair), Prof. Xinglong Zhang (Co-Chair), Prof. Hung Wing Li, Prof. Hairong Lyu, Prof. Qisi Wang, Prof. Qingyun Wan&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;    &lt;p&gt;&#10;        &lt;strong&gt;Advisory Board:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#10;        Prof. Chunshan Song, Prof. Hua Zhang, Prof. To Ngai&#10;    &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;    &lt;footer&gt;&#10;        &amp;copy; Forum 2026 Organizing Committee&#10;        &amp;nbsp;|&amp;nbsp; Design by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mikepierce&quot;&gt;Mike Pierce&lt;/a&gt;&#10;    &lt;/footer&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;/body&gt;&#10;&lt;/html&gt;&#10;&#10;" />
            </PendingDiffInfo>
          </value>
        </entry>
